   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>The role of the logged-in user should be <uicontrol>Fund Manager</uicontrol>.</li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>After creating a global fund list, you can submit the  <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol> record for approval.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Enterprise Dashboard</uicontrol> is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand the <uicontrol>Fund Management</uicontrol> folder, and then click <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>GLOBAL FUND LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To approve the <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol>  record, perform the following steps:</p>
            <p>
               <note>The following steps cover only the positive and forward   workflow actions to reach the  <uicontrol>Approved</uicontrol> status.</note>
            </p>
            <p>
               <table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <tgroup cols="3">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="10%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="25%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="65%"/>
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Phase</entry>
                           <entry>Role </entry>
                           <entry>Workflow Steps</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>1</entry>
                           <entry morerows="1">Fund Manager</entry>
                           <entry>
                              <ol>
                                 <li>
                                    <p>In the  list page, select the appropriate record that is in the <uicontrol>Draft</uicontrol> workflow status, and then click <uicontrol>Select Actions</uicontrol>.</p>
                                 </li>
                                 <li>
                                    <p>Click <uicontrol>Submit</uicontrol>, and in the <uicontrol>Mind</uicontrol> dialog box, click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</p>
                                    <p>The workflow status of the record is set to <uicontrol>Submitted</uicontrol>.</p>
                                 </li>
                              </ol>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>2</entry>
                           <entry>
                              <ol>
                                 <li>
                                    <p>In the  list page, select the appropriate record that is in the <uicontrol>Submitted</uicontrol> workflow status, and then click <uicontrol>Select Actions</uicontrol>.</p>
                                 </li>
                                 <li>
                                    <p>Click <uicontrol>Approve</uicontrol>, and in the <uicontrol>Mind</uicontrol> dialog box, click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</p>
                                    <p>The workflow status of the record is set to <uicontrol>Approved</uicontrol>.</p>
                                 </li>
                              </ol>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
